CGHS in Kruskal gauge 

In the previous section, we derived the CGHS entropy bound with
manifestly covariant equations of motion and entropy conditions.
However, once we add the one-loop trace anomaly, we are only able
to obtain local equations of motion in conformal gauge.
Furthermore, our calculations are greatly simplified in Kruskal
gauge.  Therefore, it behooves us to rederive the CGHS result in
Kruskal gauge.

We will assume that the lightsheet moves in the decreasing  
direction.
Our results for this past-directed  lightsheet generalize simply
to the other three possible lightsheet directions.
